Organizando todas as variÃ¡veis para melho visualizaÃ§Ã£o:

d.temp = d
d.temp$proporcao_homens = d.temp$proporcao_homens * 100
d.temp$elenco_tam = d.temp$elenco_tam * 10
d.scaled = d.temp %>% 
  select(title, gross, elenco_tam, words, proporcao_homens) %>%
  mutate_each(funs(log), 2:5)
set.seed(24)

n_clusters = 4

km = d.scaled %>% 
    select(-title) %>% 
    kmeans(centers = n_clusters, nstart = 20)
d.scaled.km.long = km %>% 
    augment(d.scaled) %>%
    gather(key = "variÃ¡vel", 
           value = "valor", 
           -title, -.cluster)
d.scaled.km.long %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x=`variÃ¡vel`, y=valor, group=title, colour=.cluster)) + 
    geom_line(alpha = .5) + 
    facet_wrap(~ .cluster) 

autoplot(km, data=d.scaled, label = TRUE)

dists = d.scaled %>% 
    select(-title) %>%
